- Use `npm install express redis` to install Express and Redis.
- Initialize Redis client with `const redis = require('redis').createClient();`.
- Connect to Redis using `redis.connect()`.
- Cache data using `redis.set(key, value)` or `redis.hset(hash, field, value)`.
- Retrieve cached data using `redis.get(key)` or `redis.hget(hash, field)`.
- Set expiration for cache items with `redis.expire(key, seconds)`.
- Use middleware to cache responses: 
  ```javascript
  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    const key = req.originalUrl;
    redis.get(key, (err, data) => {
      if (data !== null) {
        res.send(data);
      } else {
        res.sendResponse = res.send;
        res.send = (body) => {
          redis.setex(key, 3600, body); // Cache for 1 hour
          res.sendResponse(body);
        };
        next();
      }
    });
  });
  ```
- Monitor Redis performance with `redis-cli --stat` or third-party tools.
- Update Express and Redis packages to their latest versions using `npm update express redis`.

